crypto

Class PiecemealBallotEncrypter

  • java.lang.Object
    • crypto.PiecemealBallotEncrypter

  • public class PiecemealBallotEncrypter
extends java.lang.Object
    Wrapper around BallotEncrypter to allow for concealing as much of the time spent encrypting as possible behind VoteBox's UI actions.

      • adderUpdate

        public void adderUpdate(java.lang.String id,
               java.util.List<ASExpression> singleCard,
               java.util.List<java.lang.String> cardGroup,
               PublicKey publicKey)
        Updates a piecemeal encryption of a ballot, if we're using Adder style ballots
        Parameters:
        id - - the id of the Card that contains the race to be updated (the card that defines the raceGroup at least)
        singleCard - - the (id [counter]) pair list to encrypt
        cardGroup - - the grouping to provide a NIZK for (redundant, but helpful for debugging)
        publicKey - - the key to use to encrypt the ballot

      • canonicalIdOrder

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.String> canonicalIdOrder()
        Provides a canonical ordering of the ids found in _voteCache. Necessary given the uncertainty of which order the ballot will be traversed in, to say nothing of concurrency concerns and call orders.
        Returns:
        the order to traverse the _voteCache in while building the final ballot and/or the random list
